\pard\plain\s4\ql\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\b\fs32\sl240\slmult1 \sb120 \fi0 3.3  Quantum Bit Example\par
\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs22\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 We can demonstrate some of the strange qualities of the qubit easily using the mathematical representation introduced above. We shall consider a trine. This is simply the name given to a qubit that can be in one of the three states listed below and can be thought of as an extension of the classical bit, but with limitations on the qubit. {\par
